if you have soothe, one of my fave new tricks for making noise and stuff sound more pleasing, get some sine waves and put em in all the notes that are out of the key your track is in, bounce that and sidechain your noisy stuff so it takes out those frequencies a bit (exaggerated in this example)
9:54 PM
i found it very helpful for cleaning up long lush reverb tails so they dont overpower things as much with a wall of noise

11:17 AM
